From f4fcf1472edf56c984d24eddada0fff63922d11f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Date: Wed, 17 Sep 2025 19:58:14 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Backport CVE-2024-32619 fix to HDF5 1.10.8

This commit backports the security fix for CVE-2024-32619, which addresses
a heap-based buffer overflow in H5T_copy_reopen in H5T.c.

Changes made:
- H5T__unlock_cb: Added null check for dt->shared before accessing state
- H5T__close_cb: Removed assertion for dt->shared, added null check
- H5T_close_real: Added null check for dt->shared before accessing state
- H5T_close: Added null check for dt->shared before accessing state

These defensive programming changes prevent crashes when dealing with
partially initialized datatypes during library shutdown, which was the
root cause of the heap buffer overflow vulnerability.

Original fix commit: 5f36553713 (from HDF5 1.14.5)
CVE: CVE-2024-32619
---
