 H5T__conv_struct_opt in H5Tconv.c. The root cause is insufficient
 validation of compound datatype fields during decoding from file.
 Malformed HDF5 files with duplicate compound field names or zero-sized
 array dimensions can trigger the overflow when the datatype conversion
 path is exercised. This patch adds input validation checks in the
 datatype decoder (H5Odtype.c) to reject such malformed data early,
 preventing the heap overflow from being reached.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/HDFGroup/hdf5/commit/ce53bc020d37e10a06a59501c45f1ab82539f0c5
